<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-07-06T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-07-06T18:00:00-05:00" n="646" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d646">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860c.516/94: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Poland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-07-06T19:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 6,
                                        1921—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>156. Legations 150, June 24, 9 pm.</p>
                        <p>Provided Polish Government grants equitable treatment to American banks
                            willing to do business in Poland in accordance with law of <pb facs="0794" n="698" xml:id="pg_698"/> March 23, 1920, by permitting
                            them to join syndicate of paying banks in Poland, the Department offers
                            no objection to the order indicated.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>